{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":23263,"record_hash":"sha256:aa080d4e0252fa54507fa908a6a40cc3919a1d0238facccb88b69519b33b800b","timestamp":"2026-05-11T08:13:03.080Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"I checked the current Claude Code and Codex hook docs. The short version: yes, there is a very natural lifecycle integration here, and it argues for a small dedicated hook command rather than using our current human-facing `capture` command directly.\n\n**What The Hooks Give Us**\nBoth agents expose exactly the two fields we need: `transcript_path` and `cwd`.\n\nClaude Code command hooks receive JSON on stdin, and common fields include `session_id`, `transcript_path`, and `cwd` ([Claude hooks reference](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/hooks)). Codex hooks do the same: every command hook receives JSON on stdin, with common fields including `session_id`, `transcript_path`, `cwd`, `hook_event_name`, and `model` ([Codex hooks docs](https://developers.openai.com/codex/hooks)).\n\nThat means we do not need session discovery for hook integration. The hook payload can be our source of truth.\n\n**Best Hook Points**\nFor periodic capture, `Stop` is the obvious first hook:\n\n- Claude Code `Stop` runs when Claude finishes responding, though not on user interrupt/API failure ([Claude Stop docs](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/hooks)).\n- Codex `Stop` runs at turn end and includes `last_assistant_message` and `turn_id` ([Codex Stop docs](https://developers.openai.com/codex/hooks)).\n\nFor stronger coverage later:\n\n- Claude Code `SessionEnd` is tempting, but it has a tight default timeout of 1.5s, so I would not make it the primary capture point yet ([Claude SessionEnd docs](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/hooks)).\n- `UserPromptSubmit` could capture before each new prompt, which is nice for incremental durability.\n- `PreCompact` / `PostCompact` are interesting later for preserving context around compaction, especially for handoff.\n\n**Important Gotcha**\nI would not wire the existing `but agentlog capture` command directly into hooks.\n\nOur current command prints human output like `Captured 3 records`. Codex `Stop` expects JSON on stdout if stdout is present, and plain text is invalid for that event ([Codex Stop docs](https://developers.openai.com/codex/hooks)). Claude hooks also interpret stdout/stderr in event-specific ways.\n\nSo the better shape is a hook-safe command that is quiet by default:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog hook [--agent codex|claude] [--associate-target <target>]\n```\n\nIt would:\n\n- read one hook JSON object from stdin\n- extract `cwd` and `transcript_path`\n- no-op successfully if `transcript_path` is missing/null\n- use explicit `--agent` or existing environment detection\n- call the same underlying `record_transcript`\n- produce no stdout on success\n- avoid blocking/continuation JSON entirely\n- write only minimal stderr on unexpected failures, or maybe swallow non-critical capture failures so hooks do not disrupt the agent\n\n**Config Direction**\nBoth agents support repo-local hook config:\n\n- Claude Code can use `.claude/settings.json`, which is shareable when committed ([Claude hook locations](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/hooks-guide)).\n- Codex can use `<repo>/.codex/hooks.json` or `<repo>/.codex/config.toml`; hooks require `codex_hooks = true` ([Codex hook docs](https://developers.openai.com/codex/hooks)).\n\nA later installer command could be useful:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog hook install --agent codex --scope project\nbut agentlog hook install --agent claude --scope project\n```\n\nBut I would not start there. First build the quiet `hook` entrypoint, then manually document example hook configs. Installer code can wait until we know the exact behavior we want.\n\nMy recommendation: add a short lifecycle-integration doc first, then implement `but agentlog hook` as the smallest bridge from hook stdin to our existing capture pipeline.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T08:13:03.080Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}